1
00:00:00,399 --> 00:00:04,706
Umm..

2
00:00:04,706 --> 00:00:06,751
I don't know this chord, Eira..

3
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:08,266
Ofnadwy...

4
00:00:08,617 --> 00:00:10,420
It's a B major..

5
00:00:10,771 --> 00:00:12,128
Anywho,

6
00:00:12,128 --> 00:00:24,303
The beat goes like this.

7
00:00:24,653 --> 00:00:29,681
Mam says Tad's packed too many jumpers again,

8
00:00:29,681 --> 00:00:34,228
Ma just laughs, says, “Well, that’s our man.”

9
00:00:34,228 --> 00:00:38,777
Teema’s got mud up her knees by ten,

10
00:00:38,777 --> 00:00:43,963
I've got stickers on the frying pan.

11
00:00:43,963 --> 00:00:48,670
The cabin creaks when the front door swings,

12
00:00:48,670 --> 00:00:53,457
The kettle’s christened “Llewelyn the Hot.”

13
00:00:53,457 --> 00:00:58,244
I burn the pasta, they all still sing,

14
00:00:58,244 --> 00:01:03,430
We light a candle in a camping pot.

15
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:06,063
There’s a cricket stuck in the kettle box,

16
00:01:06,063 --> 00:01:09,016
Mam says it’s luck — or possibly rot.

17
00:01:09,016 --> 00:01:13,644
Ma says “Let’s just survive the night,”

18
00:01:13,644 --> 00:01:21,671
Teema says “What if there’s foxes that bite?”

19
00:01:22,021 --> 00:01:26,250
Foxes in the garden, don’t make a sound

20
00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:26,269
Let the wind and the dark do the talking

21
00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:30,079
They leave no tracks, just a shimmered bend

22
00:01:30,079 --> 00:01:31,277
now

23
00:01:31,277 --> 00:01:34,867
They leave no tracks, just a shimmered

24
00:01:34,867 --> 00:01:36,063
bend

25
00:01:36,063 --> 00:01:40,052
Some songs you sing without knowing when

26
00:01:40,052 --> 00:01:46,676
We sit outside with our socks mismatched,

27
00:01:46,676 --> 00:01:50,903
Thermos tea and a sky that cracked.

28
00:01:50,903 --> 00:01:56,250
I see stars, Teema sees smoke,

29
00:01:56,250 --> 00:02:00,718
Eric swears he saw the moon wear a cloak.

30
00:02:00,718 --> 00:02:04,947
“Tell us a story,” Teema and I plead —

31
00:02:04,947 --> 00:02:08,616
Steph pulls her sleeves and begins to weave:

32
00:02:08,616 --> 00:02:14,600
“There’s a fox that walks where the starlight breaks,

33
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:19,706
And he only appears when the whole world aches.”

34
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:25,052
Teema goes still. My eyes go wide.

35
00:02:25,052 --> 00:02:28,085
“Do they sing?” I ask. “Or just hide?”

36
00:02:28,085 --> 00:02:34,149
“Eira, some sing,” says Steph. “But only slow.

37
00:02:34,149 --> 00:02:37,580
Only for those who’ll never let go.”

38
00:02:37,580 --> 00:02:43,883
Foxes in the garden, slow your breath

39
00:02:43,883 --> 00:02:48,431
Hear the song in the nettle’s depth

40
00:02:48,431 --> 00:02:53,138
They don’t wear shoes, they don’t leave names

41
00:02:53,138 --> 00:02:57,048
They pass like dreams, and play no games

42
00:02:57,048 --> 00:03:15,000
Later on, when the girls are down,

43
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:20,425
Ma’s reading, Mam’s curled in a sleepy frown.

44
00:03:20,425 --> 00:03:24,574
I step out, just for air,

45
00:03:24,574 --> 00:03:30,000
And the garden hums like a whispered prayer.

46
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:34,548
Two shadows flicker through lavender stems,

47
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:38,058
Bronze and bone and silent hems.

48
00:03:38,058 --> 00:03:44,062
No sound, no fear — just hush and thread—

49
00:03:44,043 --> 00:03:48,909
Their eyes catch Tad's, and nothing’s said.

50
00:03:48,909 --> 00:03:53,616
I don’t call Mam. I don’t blink twice.

51
00:03:53,616 --> 00:03:58,484
Some wonders don’t survive advice.

52
00:03:58,484 --> 00:04:03,989
I let them pass like a rolling tide,

53
00:04:03,989 --> 00:04:07,100
Just lucky I was standing outside.

54
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:13,324
Foxes in the garden, gone with dawn

55
00:04:13,324 --> 00:04:17,872
But I still hear them in the yawn

56
00:04:17,872 --> 00:04:23,697
Of the floorboard creak and kettle hum —

57
00:04:23,697 --> 00:04:29,281
Some magic doesn’t need to come.

58
00:04:29,281 --> 00:04:33,829
See? Told you it was a B major.
